parameters.description: Logit of zooplankton excretion efficiency (proportion of grazed phytoplankton immediately excreted as dissolved nutrients)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton excretion efficiency representing fast nutrient recycling from grazing (proportion 0-1). This parameter captures sloppy feeding and metabolic excretion, creating a rapid nutrient regeneration pathway distinct from slower mortality-based remineralization. Typical values 0.2-0.4 based on marine zooplankton studies.

parameters.description: Logit of nutrient recycling efficiency (proportion of dead organic matter remineralized to nutrients)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Nutrient recycling efficiency (proportion 0-1)

parameters.description: Log of surface light intensity (incident photosynthetically active radiation)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Surface light intensity representing incident PAR at ocean surface (W m^-2). Typical values range from 50-500 W m^-2 depending on latitude, season, and cloud cover. Critical for determining phytoplankton photosynthesis rates in the mixed layer.

parameters.description: Log of background light attenuation coefficient (water and dissolved matter)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Background light attenuation coefficient (m^-1) representing absorption and scattering by water molecules and dissolved organic matter. Typical oceanic values 0.04-0.2 m^-1 for clear water, higher in coastal regions.

parameters.description: Log of specific light attenuation coefficient by phytoplankton (self-shading)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Specific attenuation coefficient for phytoplankton self-shading (m^2 g C^-1). Represents how phytoplankton biomass reduces light penetration. Typical values 0.02-0.2 m^2 g C^-1. Creates negative feedback on phytoplankton growth at high densities.

parameters.description: Log of half-saturation constant for light-limited phytoplankton growth
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation constant for light limitation (W m^-2). Light intensity at which photosynthesis rate is half of maximum. Typical values 20-80 W m^-2 for marine phytoplankton. Lower values indicate adaptation to low light conditions.

parameters.description: Log of mixed layer depth
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Mixed layer depth (m) representing the depth of the surface ocean layer with uniform properties due to wind mixing. Typical values 20-100 m, varying seasonally. Determines the average light environment experienced by phytoplankton.
